<HEADLINE> Sixers Waive Benjamin, Sign Mahorn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- The Philadelphia 76ers waived center Benoit  
Benjamin and signed 40-year-old free-agent Rick Mahorn, who played 
for the team nine years ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Mahorn spent his last two seasons with the Detroit Pistons, who  
he played for from 1985-89 before joining the 76ers for the first 
time. He broke in with the Washington Bullets in 1980. 
</P>
<P>
	Mahorn helped the Pistons win the NBA title in 1989 as a member  
of the ``Bad Boy'' squad. 
</P>
<P>
	Benjamin saw scant playing time this season and averaged just  
0.7 points and 1.3 rebounds a game. 
