<HEADLINE> Justice Blackmun Has Hip Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Retired Supreme Court Justice Harry A.  
Blackmun underwent hip replacement surgery Tuesday after falling 
and breaking his hip, a court spokeswoman said today. 
</P>
<P>
	Blackmun, 90, was resting comfortably after the surgery at  
Arlington Hospital in suburban Arlington, Va., said court 
spokeswoman Kathy Arberg. 
</P>
<P>
	She said Blackmun suffered a fracture to his left hip from a  
fall at his home on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``After surgery yesterday he told everyone (on his court staff)  
to get back to work,'' Ms. Arberg said. ``He was conversational, 
obviously, and alert after surgery.'' 
</P>
<P>
	His wife, Dottie, and three daughters were with him, she said.  
</P>
<P>
	Blackmun was named to the court by President Nixon in 1970 and  
retired in 1994. He is best known as the author of the 1973 Roe vs. 
Wade decision that legalized abortion nationwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
