Helsinki, Finland, and Stojko does not feel he is healthy enough to 
compete in three major competitions so close together. 
</P>
<P>
	While the ISU has not issued a definitive answer, Cinquanta  
indicated his group would respect Stojko's decision. 
</P>
<P>
	``We have a duty to respect the dignity of the skater. If a  
</P>
