<DOCNO> APW19990224.0053 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-24 10:26:29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	
</P>
<P>
	In the spotlight: Ron Howard  
</P>
<P>
	 *Image:* If Quentin Tarantino is the Mr. Cool of American  
cinema, then Ron Howard is its King of Corn: the sweet, sincere 
square whose films have made his name synonymous with 
sentimentality. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Personal stats:* Howard was born in Duncan, Okla., on March 1,  
1954. He grew up in Los Angeles and attended the University of 
Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Acting:* He made his stage debut with his parents when he was  
18 months old. When he was 6, Howard got the role of Opie Taylor on 
television's ``The Andy Griffith Show.'' He graduated to Richie 
Cunningham of ``Happy Days,'' the teen-age geek with the goofy 
grin. 
</P>
<P>
	He also appeared as the wholesome teen-ager of the classic  
George Lucas film, ``American Graffiti.'' 
</P>
<P>
	 *Directing:* Howard directed his first film, ``Grand Theft  
Auto,'' in 1977. The film, shot in 20 days, was a typical car-crash 
action movie. But it grossed $15 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Howard's list of hits includes ``Splash,'' ``Cocoon,''  
``Parenthood,'' ``Backdraft,'' ``Far and Away,'' ``The Paper,'' 
``Apollo 13'' and ``Ransom.'' 
</P>
<P>
	His new film, ``EDtv,'' stars Matthew McConaughey, Jenna Elfman,  
Ellen DeGeneres and Woody Harrelson. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Quote:* ``I'm probably as happy as I've ever been. My movies  
are dealing with more serious themes. I ask myself, did the same 
guy make 'Splash' and 'Backdraft'?'' 

</P>
<P>
	Celebrity birthdays for Feb. 28-March 6:  
</P>
<P>
	Feb. 28: Actor Charles Durning is 76. Actor Gavin MacLeod is 68.  
Actress Bernadette Peters is 51. Actress Mercedes Ruehl is 51. 
Actor John Turturro is 42. Actor Robert Sean Leonard is 30. 
</P>
<P>
	March 1: Singer Harry Belafonte is 72. Actor Robert Conrad is  
64. Singer Roger Daltrey is 55. Actor Alan Thicke is 52. 
Actor-director Ron Howard is 45. Actress Catherine Bach (``The 
Dukes of Hazzard'') is 45. Actor Tim Daly (``Wings'') is 43. Actor 
Mark-Paul Gosselaar (``Hyperion Bay'') is 25. 
