<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> McGwire Brings Out Fans, Media </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JUPITER, Fla. (AP) -- It was just like last year for Mark  
McGwire. 
</P>
<P>
	The home run king chuckled and shook his head in wonder when he  
sat down today in front of a microphone. Fans had crowded against 
fences to watch him go through the Cardinals' first full-squad 
workout of the spring, and about 100 reporters came to his first 
news conference. 
</P>
<P>
	``I couldn't believe the turnout from the fans,'' McGwire said.  
``That was amazing. Then all of you guys. I've never been in a 
first day of spring training like this ever.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Neither had the Cardinals, who drew about 20 reporters for their  
first workout last year. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire's news conference lasted about an hour and included the  
revelation that the most pressure he felt last fall came after he 
broke Maris' record and worried about keeping it from the 
fast-charging Sammy Sosa. 
</P>
<P>
	All last fall, McGwire had maintained that he didn't care who  
ended up with more homers. 
</P>
<P>
	Told that new teammate Carlos Baerga thought McGwire was capable  
of hitting 80 homers this year, McGwire laughed again. 
</P>
<P>
	``Geez, I'd definitely retire if I did that,'' he said.  
</P>
<P>
	He also doesn't plan to stop taking the muscle-building  
supplement androstenedione. 
</P>
<P>
	``Major league baseball is not the IOC,'' McGwire said,  
referring to the International Olympic Committee's ban on 
androstenedione. ``And it has absolutely nothing to do with me 
hitting a baseball. I don't endorse the produce. I never did. 
Someone stuck a nose in my locker.'' 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire, who kept a low profile for most of the offseason, said  
he'd like to play at least five more years, but that he would 
``walk away'' from baseball if there was another work stoppage. The 
current agreement is likely to expire after the 2001 season. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire also criticized reports of security measures the  
Cardinals are taking to protect him. 
</P>
<P>
	``No, I do not have bodyguards,'' he said in his opening remark.  
``I don't need any bodyguards. I don't want any.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
