<HEADLINE> P&AMP;G May Sell Coast Soap Brand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Procter &AMP; Gamble Co. says it might sell its  
Coast brand of bar soap, which was introduced nationally in 1976. 
</P>
<P>
	P&AMP;G said Wednesday it is soliciting offers but will keep the  
brand if no acceptable bid is received. 
</P>
<P>
	The brand, now sold throughout North America, is profitable but  
does not fit into P&AMP;G's long-term business plans, management said. 
</P>
<P>
	The company's skin care and cosmetics unit prefers to focus on  
its global brands such as Oil of Olay, Zest and Safeguard, said 
Robert Blanchard, president of the unit. 
</P>
<P>
	In recent years, P&AMP;G has sold -- or offered for sale -- several  
brands that management believes do not have potential for worldwide 
sales increases. 
</P>
<P>
	If P&AMP;G sells Coast, the company expects to reassign most of its  
employees now working in the unit. 
</P>
<P>
	Coast represented less than 1 percent of P&AMP;G's total sales of  
beauty care products for the fiscal year ended June 30, 1998. The 
Cincinnati-based consumer products company had worldwide sales of 
$37.2 billion for that fiscal year. 

</P>
</TEXT>
