<HEADLINE> Match Play Glance  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CARLSBAD, Calif. (AP) -- A brief look at the Match Play matches  
Wednesday at La Costa Resort. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Who's Left:* Tiger Woods, David Duval and 30 of the world's  
best golfers. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Who's Out:* Davis Love III, Ernie Els, Colin Montgomerie, among  
five of the world's top 10 players. 
</P>
<P>
	 *What's next:* The field shrinks to 16 after Thursday's  
second-round matches. 
</P>
<P>
	 *At stake:* $5 million for the field, $1 million to the winner.  
Even the first-round losers took home $25,000. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Shot of the Day:* Tiger Woods, putting an 8-iron to within a  
foot after Nick Faldo got within birdie range on the 10th hole. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Noteworthy:* All four players from the United Kingdom lost  
their first-round matches: Nick Faldo, Darren Clarke, Colin 
Montgomerie and Lee Westwood. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Quoteworthy:* ``I like match play. It makes it easy for me  
knowing I don't have to play my foul balls.'' -- Steve Pate after 
beating Davis Love III. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Match of the Day:* Jose Maria Olazabal losing the first two  
holes and trailing 2-down after six to Billy Mayfair. Olazabal then 
won five of the next six holes before closing Olazabal out 5 and 3. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Key pairings:* Vijay Singh vs. Bernhard Langer, 12:30 p.m.;  
Justin Leonard vs. Shigeki Maruyama, 12:57 p.m.; Tiger Woods vs. 
Bob Tway, 1:42 p.m.; David Duval vs. Bill Glasson, 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Television:* Thursday, 2-6 p.m. EST, ESPN.  
</P>
