<HEADLINE> London Shares Close at New High / British Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Buoyed by the Prime Minister Tony Blair's euro  
plans and a stream of strong company results, share prices surged 
to a record high Wednesday on the London Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index rose 152.4  
points, or 2.4 percent, to 6,307.6. 
</P>
<P>
	Provisional volume was 999.2 million shares, compared with 922.4  
million shares Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The closing eclipsed the previous record of 6,179, set on July  
20, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts cited strong profits reported by top companies over the  
last two days, and the prospect of Britain joining the single 
European currency sooner rather than later, as suggested by the 
National Changeover Plan proposed Tuesday by Blair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
