<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Magazine: Lewinsky Recalls Terror </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Monica Lewinsky recalled feelings of terror  
during the past year and partly blames Linda Tripp for having made 
her feel suicidal, according to TV Guide interviews with the two 
journalists who have talked with her. 
</P>
<P>
	The former White House intern reportedly told Jon Snow of  
Britain's Channel Four her despondency in the aftermath of her 
relationship with President Clinton was partly the result of 
actions by Mrs. Tripp, who secretly recorded their telephone 
conversations. 
</P>
<P>
	``She (Lewinsky) literally runs out of damnation for Tripp,''  
Snow says in the March 6 issue of TV Guide. 
</P>
<P>
	He and ABC News' Barbara Walters -- the only journalists to have  
interviewed Ms. Lewinsky -- spoke to the magazine about their 
separate interviews with her. 
</P>
<P>
	In a news release Tuesday, the magazine quotes Snow as saying  
Ms. Lewinsky disclosed the ``very specific moment when she did feel 
suicidal'' and said Mrs. Tripp contributed to her despair. 
</P>
<P>
	Walters, whose interview will air in a two-hour broadcast of  
``20/20'' on March 3, said she addressed allegations that Marcia 
Lewis condoned her daughter's relationship with the president. 
</P>
<P>
	``Monica feels that her mother has been misportrayed. This is  
very painful for Monica,'' Walters says in the magazine. ``(Monica) 
could not have gotten through this year without her.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Tripp said on CNN's ``Larry King Live'' last week that the  
former intern became suicidal not merely as a result of Clinton 
``dumping her'' but out of fear he would learn she had confided to 
others about the relationship. 
</P>
<P>
	Snow's interview will air March 4 on Britain's Channel Four and  
in 32 other countries. TV Guide said the British station paid a 
``reported $600,000'' for the interview, and ABC paid nothing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
