<HEADLINE> Knee Surgery for Astros' Alou Set </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KISSIMMEE, Fla. (AP) -- Houston Astros outfielder Moises Alou  
will have surgery March 3 to repair damage to the anterior cruciate 
ligament in his left knee. 
</P>
<P>
	Alou was hurt last Thursday at his home in the Dominican  
Republic when he lost his balance trying to adjust a treadmill that 
was going too fast. He hoped the injury was not serious, but an MRI 
in Houston on Monday revealed the damage. 
</P>
<P>
	The surgery will be performed by Dr. Richard Steadman in Vail,  
Colo. 
</P>
<P>
	Alou, 32, hit .312 with 38 home runs and 124 RBIs last year and  
finished third in the NL MVP voting behind Sammy Sosa and Mark 
McGwire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
