<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-24 18:33:09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Frerotte, Seahawks Like Each Other </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KIRKLAND, Wash. (AP) -- The Seahawks like Gus Frerotte -- and he  
likes them. 
</P>
<P>
	Money is what's stopping the former Washington Redskins'  
quarterback, now a free agent, from signing with Seattle 
immediately. 
</P>
<P>
	``As is usually the case, when you talk the first time, there's  
a little difference of opinion,'' new Seahawks coach-general 
manager Mike Holmgren said Wednesday. ``This is no different.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Frerotte, 27, said he enjoyed his two-day visit and workout, but  
still plans to visit Detroit and Chicago. He plans to work out for 
the Lions this week and the Bears next week. 
</P>
<P>
	The Seahawks have ``proposed something, but it's just something  
we want to take a little more time to look at and think about right 
now,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Down to one quarterback, Jon Kitna, after releasing Warren Moon  
and John Friesz, the Seahawks were hoping to lure Doug Pederson, 
Holmgren's backup quarterback in Green Bay, to Seattle as a free 
agent. 
</P>
<P>
	But Pederson signed last week with the Philadelphia Eagles.  
</P>
<P>
	The Seahawks have created $1.3 million of salary cap room by  
restructuring the contracts of free safety Darryl Williams and 
offensive tackle Howard Ballard. 
</P>
<P>
	The team is trying to restructure several other contracts.  
</P>
<P>
	Senior vice president Mike Reinfeldt, who followed Holmgren to  
Seattle from Green Bay, talked to Ralph Cindrich, Frerotte's agent. 
</P>
<P>
	``I kind of think he would like to be here,'' Reinfeldt said.  
``He's a good fit for us. I think all else being equal, he comes 
here.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Holmgren developed Brett Favre in Green Bay and it sounds like  
if the Seahawks come up with the right money, he'll get a chance to 
resurrect Frerotte's career in Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
	``Coach Holmgren has such a good reputation as a quarterbacks  
coach and he is really a winner,'' Frerotte said. ``He's been to 
the Super Bowl. Ever since you were a little kid, you dream about 
playing in a Super Bowl and I think it's a great opportunity to get 
there.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Frerotte, a Pro Bowler for Washington in 1996, was released by  
the Redskins this month. The Redskins avoided paying him a $1.25 
million roster bonus. 
</P>
<P>
	At Washington, where he was a seventh-round draft choice in  
1994, he started 45 games, including one last season when he lost 
his starting job to Trent Green. 
</P>
<P>
	If Frerotte joins the Seahawks, he would be given a chance to  
start. Kitna replaced Moon as Seattle's starting quarterback for 
the final five games last season under fired coach Dennis Erickson. 
</P>
<P>
	Holmgren wants to bring four quarterbacks to training camp.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
