<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gardner Joins AP Board of Directors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Frank Gardner, senior vice president for  
television at Scripps Howard Broadcasting Company, has been 
appointed to The Associated Press Board of Directors. 
</P>
<P>
	The AP board of directors is a 24-member body representing its  
newspaper and broadcast members in overseeing the activities and 
strategic direction of the not-for-profit cooperative. 
</P>
<P>
	Gardner, 56, oversees the Scripps Howard station group and the  
company's fast-growing cable TV division, which includes Home &AMP; 
Garden Television, the Food Network and Cinetel Productions, a 
producer of cable television programming that is soon to be renamed 
Scripps Howard Productions. 
</P>
<P>
	He rejoined Scripps Howard Broadcasting Company in 1993 from Fox  
Broadcasting Company, where he was senior vice president of news 
programming. His Fox tenure followed an affiliation with Scripps 
stations dating back to 1976. 
</P>
<P>
	Scripps Howard Broadcasting operates NBC affiliates in Tulsa,  
Kansas City and West Palm Beach; ABC affiliates in Cincinnati, 
Cleveland, Detroit, Phoenix, Tampa and Baltimore. 
</P>
<P>
	A membership cooperative founded in 1848, The Associated Press  
is the world's oldest and largest news-gathering organization. With 
headquarters in New York, AP provides news, photos, graphics, audio 
and video to more than 15,000 newspapers and broadcast outlets 
worldwide. 




</P>
</TEXT>
