<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest Ground Workers OK Pacts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAGAN, Minn. (AP) -- New contracts have been approved for about  
18,000 Northwest Airlines ground workers. 
</P>
<P>
	The International Association of Machinists said Tuesday that  
the contracts were ratified by about 69 percent of the 13,742 
members who voted Feb. 16. The contracts will be signed Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The agreements cover three groups of employees -- about 10,000  
ticket agents, reservationists and clerks; about 8,000 baggage 
handlers and other ramp equipment operators; and about 40 security 
guards. 
</P>
<P>
	The new agreement includes a 14 percent wage increase over four  
years, a 3.5 percent lump-sum retroactive payment, a 50 percent 
increase in pensions and additional job security. 
</P>
<P>
	Northwest still has open contracts with two other large employee  
groups -- 10,000 flight attendants and 10,000 mechanics and 
cleaners. Negotiations with mechanics won't resume until a union 
representation election is settled. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
