<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Turner Readies Southeast TV Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Turner Broadcasting System today announced plans  
for a new regional TV network meant for southeastern viewers, 
featuring shows about Southern lifestyles, country music and pro 
wrestling. 
</P>
<P>
	The Turner South channel will draw upon the Turner movie and TV  
series library, along with original Southern-flavored shows and 
games of the company's pro sports franchises -- the Atlanta Braves 
in baseball, the Hawks in basketball and the Thrashers hockey 
franchise that debuts next season. 
</P>
<P>
	Among the new programs planned are a weekly show of country  
music from Nashville's Bluebird Cafe, a weekly series developed 
with Southern Living magazine, ``The College Show'' using tapes 
submitted from regional campus stations, and ``WCW Classics'' with 
pro wrestling favorites. 
</P>
<P>
	Bill Burke, president of TBS Superstation, will head the new  
network, which will be launched this fall. TBS is a division of 
Time Warner Inc., where Ted Turner now serves as vice chairman. 
</P>
<P>
	Burke said targeting Turner Broadcasting's home region, where  
many people retain a strong regional identity, will hopefully prove 
popular and profitable. 
</P>
<P>
	``We think it makes a lot of sense,'' Burke said at a news  
conference today. ``The Turner brand is incredibly strong in this 
region, and it's a very natural region for us.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Turner South will offer movies in a show called ``Kudzu  
Theater-Movies that Grow on You,'' a play on the ever-spreading 
regional vine. 
</P>
<P>
	Burke said that not only do Southern-themed shows such as ``Andy  
Griffith'' play particularly well in the region, some movies such 
as ``Dumb and Dumber,'' a slapstick comedy without a regional link, 
have gotten unusually high ratings locally. 
</P>
<P>
	The company will step up talks with cable operators to secure  
space and expect its long-standing regional relationships to help 
those efforts. Burke said the network could potentially reach 6 
million homes in Georgia, Alabama, Mississippi, Tennessee, North 
Carolina and South Carolina. 
</P>
<P>
	Burke said Turner Broadcasting has regional TV rights to its  
sports franchises and doesn't expect any conflicts with existing 
network deals. 
</P>
<P>
	The new network joins the wide-ranging lineup of 18 TV networks  
for Turner Broadcasting. 
</P>
<P>
	The company began with Atlanta-based TBS, which Ted Turner  
developed into the first ``superstation'' in 1976 by using 
satellite to reach homes around the nation, and followed with CNN, 
TNT and other news, sports and entertainment networks. Its newest 
entertainment network is Turner Classic Movies, launched five years 
ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
