<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Wohlers Impressive in Comeback </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KISSIMMEE, Fla. (AP) -- Former Atlanta Braves closer Mark  
Wohlers, trying to rebound from a dismal season, had the most 
impressive performance of his comeback Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	``He looks goooood,'' Ozzie Guillen said after swinging and  
missing a split-finger fastball from Wohlers during batting 
practice. 
</P>
<P>
	Chipper Jones stood with the bat on his shoulder, frozen by a  
Wohlers fastball. 
</P>
<P>
	``That was some cheese right there,'' Jones said. ``Way to go,  
Wo!'' 
</P>
<P>
	While throwing several pitches in the dirt and admitting he  
wasn't working at full speed, Wohlers was pleased by his 
performance. He used all of his pitches -- also throwing the slider 
-- and generally was around the plate. 
</P>
<P>
	``I know I'm on the right path,'' said Wohlers, who inexplicably  
lost the ability to throw strikes last season, finishing with a 
10.18 ERA for the Braves and a 20.43 ERA during a stint in 
Triple-A. ``I can see the light at the end of the tunnel. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've got to be cautious. I realize there's going to be bumps  
along the way. But each time out there, I'm getting better and 
better.'' 
</P>
<P>
	During his first appearance of spring training last week,  
Wohlers nearly threw a pitch over the batting cage, continuously 
skipped the ball in the dirt and hit a batter twice. But he looked 
much sharper on Monday, and followed up with an even better 
performance Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	When he left the mound, the crowd of several hundred at Walt  
Disney's Wide World of Sports Stadium gave him a lengthy ovation. 
</P>
<P>
	``That was nice,'' he said. ``The support has been great. It's  
putting a little more fire in my engine.'' 
</P>
<P>
 *NOTES:* The Braves announced five more signings Wednesday, agreeing  
to one-year contracts with pitchers Kerry Ligtenberg, Bruce Chen, 
Odalis Perez, Damian Moss, along with outfielder George Lombard. 
... There are still three unsigned players on the 40-man roster: 
pitcher Kevin Millwood, outfielder Andruw Jones and first baseman 
Randall Simon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
